      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>thighs</strong>, skin-side down with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>dried thyme </strong>(save the rest for later!) and cook for 3-4 min or until browned</p>",
